4. Rinse in water and dry. 5. Eosinophil granules stain reddish-brown, mast cell granules dark blue. Neutrophils and macrophages should not have any cytoplasmic staining. I. 2. 3. 4. 3.6.3. Luxol-Fast-Blue Stain the fixed slide for 1.5 h in Luxol-Fast-Blue. Wash under gently running tapwater for 3 min. Dry. Stain with Harris Hematoxylin for 2 min (30 s for cytocentrifuge
